# Commit Message Template — CleanCity Group 15
# Version: 2.0 | Effective: 2025-11-06
# CCR Format: CCR-###
#
# Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <message> (CCR-###)
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): implement JWT authentication (CCR-010)
# fix(ui): correct dashboard filter state reset (CCR-011)
# docs(governance): add QA Governance Policy (CCR-002)
# test(e2e): update pickup scheduling tests (CCR-021)
#
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Commit Types
# -------------------------------------------------------
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# test:     Adding or updating tests
# refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# qa:       QA improvement or audit fix
# ci:       Changes to CI/CD configuration or scripts
# chore:    Maintenance, dependencies, or tooling
#
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Scope Examples (use component/module name)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# auth | dashboard | feedback | governance | migration | e2e | qa | docs
#
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Guidelines:
# - Reference one or more Functional Requirement IDs if applicable (FR-###)
# - Keep subject line under 72 characters
# - Use present tense (“add”, “fix”, not “added”, “fixed”)
# - Leave the body blank or add details below after a blank line
#
# Example Full Commit:
#
# docs(migration): add CleanCity migration mapping for repo restructure (CCR-003)
#
# - Maps each test and document to enterprise repo structure
# - Linked to FR-014, FR-021
#
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Subject line (one line summary):
#
#
# Commit body (optional, details or references):
#
